Global functions forNHN governance configuration.

* `nhn-tjeneste-types` — service-type tag set used by the governance tree (the three "tjeneste" variants, incl. casing drift). Distinct from the full Extract-2 service-type set, which also includes `Tiltak`/`Satsning for fart` (NHN-level initiatives).
* `nhn-gov-root-filter` — root of the Styringsstruktur.
* `nhn-is-service` / `nhn-is-division` — kind tests used to dispatch children (a division is tagged `Divisjon` but not `Domene`).
* `nhn-structural-children` — sub-divisions + services tagged the current node (NHN → divisions → services).
* `nhn-objective-children` — objectives (Målsetting) attached to a structural node; suppressed under OKR nodes so results are not duplicated.
* `nhn-result-children` — key results (Resultat) attached under their Målsetting only.
* `nhn-gov-children` — the governance + intentions tree relation, used by the navigation sidebar.

Known v1 simplifications: the partially-applied `Domene` layer is not yet shown; some month-prefixed review tiddlers carry a service-type tag and will appear as extra service nodes (data drift).
